  <li id="comment-43697" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/00484410884571971030" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Hannah Claire</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2015/02/et-voila/#comment-43697"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2015-02-17T03:17:14-05:00">Tuesday, February 17, 2015 at 3:17 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Please lets not buy chocolate products that were produced by children not much older than our own, but rather, buy Fair Trade. (Cocoa Camino is a good brand)</p>
<p>The children working in on those plantations are very bady abused. They might be kidnapped, orphans, or parents may give up children if they can&#39;t feed them. The kids don&#39;t show up with birth certificates, and those who die, generally just get buried without a word to anyone.  </p>
<p>I heard this on the reputable CBC TV, and CBC Radio.  </p>
    </div>

