  <li id="comment-43720" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Tina</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2015/02/et-voila/#comment-43720"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2015-04-26T17:34:59-04:00">Sunday, April 26, 2015 at 5:34 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>A little over nine years ago I was Christmas shopping with my boyfriend and spotted a tiny whisk, perfect for mixing up hot cocoa in a mug.  I had just recently given up the pre-mixed stuff and started making it your way.  He made fun of me for buying it, questioning how much I&#39;d actually use it.  I broke up with him a few months later, but I still use that whisk all the time.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-43720' data-commentid="43720" data-postid="35" data-belowelement="comment-43720" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Tina" aria-label='Reply to Tina'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-45339" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.porkybuncreations.com/" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">PorkyBun</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2015/02/et-voila/#comment-45339"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2016-01-29T22:32:21-05:00">Friday, January 29, 2016 at 10:32 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>June is soo soo soo adorable ! </p>
<p>Her satisfied look urged me that I must try this recipe , and finally this morning I made it, soooooo good. I made 2 cups with 2 different unsweetened cocoa powder:</p>
<p>Hershey&#8217;s + sugar<br />
Van Honten + sugar</p>
<p>And it came out that the one with Van Honten was smoother and the one with Hershey&#8217;s was a bit sweeter. </p>
<p>Makes me want to buy all different kinds of cocoa powder just to compare. 🙂</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
